   ABOUT OPAL

   Created in 1995 by François Fort, the Lyon-based company OPAL is now
   the European leader in frames for children and adolescents as well as
   the French leader in the second pair offered by opticians.  The company
   is expanding its brand portfolio to grow with its first customers and
   is logically developing in the adult market. Since acquiring a majority
   stake in Demetz in 2015, Opal has also pursued its growth strategy in
   niche markets by investing in sports frames. In 2019, it invested in
   French manufacturing through the launch of the Bérénice collection.

